entries.femaleVariant: Hey, Kirk. Wanna talk.
Car's security – how do I get around it?
Who owns this ride?
Who's the owner?
Just an Arasaka suit from across the water. Spews cash outta every hole in his body.
Whole thing's simple – you swipe the Rayfield for me, I clear Pepe's account. Even toss in a cut for you I'm such a nice guy.
My man Rick works a parking structure by Embers, club where our Rayfield driver likes to kick it. There every Friday night like clockwork.
[Take device and stand] Agreed.
How ya been? 'Sides the biz, I mean.
How ya been?
Valentinos are seemin' jumpy.
Valentinos're seemin' jumpy. Thought you might know somethin'.
V, been a while. Spin it – whatcha need?
Cut him some slack, will ya? He'll pay – just needs some more time.
What's he owe you?
Cut him a break.
What's he owe?
Do I look like a priest that runs a charity to you?
You suggestin' I let a flaky cunt who can't keep a deal off the hook?
No, you let him off because it's me askin'.
Afraid that's client confidentiality. Call it a lot and leave it at that.
A credshark with business ethics. Sounds too good to be true.
Hah. You know me – I'm a man of the biz. So I need to know what I get out of it.
Well, Merry Fuckin' Christmas.
[Put down paper] Not sure I can pull it off.
I am no thief. Even if I wanted to, stealin' a ride like that'd be a level beyond me. Hell, two levels.
entries.maleVariant: I'm no thief. Even if I wanted to, stealin' a ride like that'd be a level beyond me – hell, two levels.

entries.femaleVariant: I do this, and Pepe's debt is squared?
[Put down paper] I do this and the debt's paid?
How am I supposed to do this? Expect me to slide under the chassis on a skateboard for a quick hotwire, fast an' easy?
entries.maleVariant: How'm I supposed to do this? Expect me to slide under the chassis on a skateboard for a quick hotwire, fast an' easy?

entries.femaleVariant: Beautiful thing is, a grand theft auto virgin like you don't need to know how. I already planned it.
Real, like? Got a problem with my neph. Seems to think runnin' with a gang's a good career choice.
Even after all the fine, upstanding people you've surrounded him with all his life?
You don't get it, he ain't like me.
Meanin' he's honest, straight up and pays his debts?
Hah. You're killin' me, V.
Yeah, I know some…
Product's their problem. Source dried up.
Dealers're flippin' shit?
Dealers just mopin' – boys at the top're flippin'. Heard they even wanna pop a delegation over to Colombia.
We are.
Can you imagine that? Our local leadheads sharin' a table with the cartel…
<mothertongue l="mex" m="hermana" b="Everything chill, " a="?"/>
Some bastard tried to mug me. I handled it.
Who? Local guy?
Hey, Kirk. Wanna talk.
Urgh, motherfucker…!
You really think somebody local'd try to mug me, Pepe?
entries.maleVariant: Ya really think somebody local'd try to mug me, Pepe?

entries.femaleVariant: I'll talk to Kirk. But then you're gonna owe me one.
Pepe asked me to talk you up.
What, he too shy to hand over the eddies hisself? Ah, tell him I don't bite. Not yet.
You borrow eddies, you gotta pay 'em back – with interest. It's common fuckin' knowledge.
I'll owe you one.
Transactions go two ways, I get that. I'll owe you a favor.
Know what, Kirk? I sometimes get the impression you forget you aren't from around here.
You avoid trouble.
Tempting... Got a nova idea already.
Pop into Heywood for the occasional visit, sure, but you live far, far away, in Pacifica.
What're you gettin' at?
Gettin' at you prolly needin' to think before you start somethin' with a local son.
Hmm... I'm open to other options.
[Take screamsheet] And...?
What's this?
Mhm...?
What's this?
Preem ride there on the page. Only four of 'em in NC as of now.
Grab a look.
One – Rayfield regional director. Two – Mayor Rhyne. Three – a rental service.
Uh-huh. And four?
Number four'll belong to my client – just as soon as you klep it for me, that is.
And his name?
How would I know? Why would I care? It's a hot item, and I know where to find it.
Course. I'm a man o' my word, you know that.
Soon as you appear, security cams shut down, gate swings up – the road is yours. Just gotta grab the Rayfield and roll out. Simple.
And your man Rick…?
Trust him like my own brother.
Honestly, shit plan.
Plan sounds shaky as fuck.
Oh? How so?
Sounds like you're lookin' for a sucker.
This ain't no setup, V. Heard you got a good head. Maybe we help each other make a few eddies.
Kirk, wheels like this got security systems. Good ones.
This bitty bop works like the key Rayfield techs use for repairs. Opens locks, bypasses identity authorization.
A skeleton key for all Rayfields in the city. Agh, c'mon, Kirk, even you don't buy that.
entries.maleVariant: A skeleton key for all Rayfields in the city. Heh, c'mon, Kirk, even you don't buy that.

entries.femaleVariant: Kabuki's tech wizards sell more magical shit than this under the counter. Have a little faith.
So... we all agreed, then?
[Take device and stand] Better keep your word.
Glad to hear it. Always said you were a bright bulb.
Best keep your word, Kirk.
Eeeaasy, V. Job's gonna pad your wallet too, y'know.
Good luck out there. We'll be in touch.
[Set broken nose]
[Stand] I'll talk to Kirk.
You ever gonna learn?
Ugh, you ever gonna get wise, Pepe?
entries.maleVariant: Huh, you ever gonna get wise, Pepe?

entries.femaleVariant: Got trouble?
Found yourself in a hole, sounds like. You need help?
entries.maleVariant: Found yourself'n a hole, sounds like. You need help?

entries.femaleVariant: C'mon, spin it – what is it now?
Spit it out.
Ah, knew I could count on you.
It's, uh, Kirk... I owe 'im. Don't pay by tomorrow, said he'd bust my legs.
An' he don't joke about that stuff. Got cartels in his corner.
You in it with Kirk?! Every man, woman and rat in Heywood knows he's a fuckin' shark.
My bro jumped the joint, deserved a hero's welcome... I know I fuck up, V.
Least tell me your brother's doin' all right.
Ah, doing his thing, you know…
So, can you help?
Head to Embers, in the Glen. Rick's in the garage, be waitin' for ya. You two'll hit it off.
Listen, V... I got a problem. Serious this time.
A little... anesthesia.
[Knock back shot]
[Sit] Heard about you and Pepe.
Hell's your problem?
What's your deal?
Kirk'll let it slide.
Kirk's lettin' it go, leavin' you be. I'm not, though – you fuckin' owe me big.
V, you savin' my life. I mean that.
So how's it gonna be, V?
And your man Rick...?
And you're savin' my life, V, truly.
A moment of pain, and you'll be set. Do it, choom.
So, you gonna help me out, V?
Prefer to stand tall? Creeps me out. Sit.
Ya got biz for me? Siddown.
Screamsheet – scope it out.
Got some grease on your shirt, there, tough guy.
Got grease on your shirt.
